    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-01-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="175"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 157.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Fish</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Bancroft</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 281.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-01-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 17, 1871.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I inclose for your information a translation of a
                    note of the 14th instant, from Baron Gerolt, and a copy of my reply of the same
                    date, in regard to the revocation of the declaration made by the government of
                    North Germany at the commencement of the existing war, exempting private
                    property on the high seas from seizure by the cruisers of North Germany.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For copies of these inclosures see <hi rend="italic">post,</hi>
                        correspondence between the Department of State and the German legation in
                        Washington.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
